@node "whatithink" "What i think about shareware"
@next "specreq"
@prev "notice"

WHAT I THINK ABOUT SHAREWARE

I released one program (M2I) some time ago in the shareware concept and
received $ 0.00 , Lire 0 , DM 0.00 and so on...
This is my second trial.... probably the first program was not useful or
user friendly (M2I was a quick and dirty solution to my need of obtaining
Imagine object files about molecules).

This time the program has been compiled @{b}without@{ub} the important @{i}Save@{ui}
functions.

To receive the @{b}registered fully functional version@{ub}, address your request to
the @{" author " link "commandaddr" 0 }

@endnode

@node "specreq" "Special requirements"
@next "desc"
@prev "whatithink"

SPECIAL REQUIREMENTS

This program uses the gadtools.library for the gadgets : it has been tested
only under Kickstart 2.1 and with Term 4.2 .

@endnode

@node "desc" "Description"
@next "howtostart"
@prev "specreq"

DESCRIPTION

This program allows you to enter a complete file spec (eg: host+path+filename)
while you are reading a message in an offline reader or while reading the
documentation of another program or an FTP link in an HTML document printed
in a magazine. Simply run the program with an optional public screen name :
default is Workbench screen.

This program operates as a stand alone utility but his output should be used
from TermComp, my other utility that speeds up a little the download
procedures giving you a special gui superimposed to the Term one. This
program drives Term using its ARexx msgport : if you use other
communication software, please send in the arexx documentation so that I
can consider writing a version of TermComp for you program.

@endnode

@node "howtostart" "How to start IFR"
@next "usage"
@prev "desc"

HOW TO START IFR

Command syntax from the shell :

IFR [public-screen-name]

public-screen-name is optional and the workbench screen is the default one.

From the Workbench : click on the IFR icon to start the program. To specify
another ScreenName select the program icon and activate the "Icons/Information"
menu : the ScreenName tooltype has already been set up for Term. Change it
and click "Save".

I have included an ARexx script to run this program from Spot using the
rexx menu hookup. You can find it in the ARexx directory.

@endnode

@node "usage" "Usage"
@next "knownbugs"
@prev "howtostart"

USAGE

Using the gadgets of its GUI you can :

- customize the list of your favorite FTP sites specifying :

       @{b}Site@{ub}
       @{b}Path@{ub}
       @{b}Filename@{ub}
       @{b}Transfer type@{ub}

  hot keys are available for these gadgets and also tab cycling string gadgets
  is enabled.

- @{b}Add@{ub} the specified @{i}Site@{ui} to your @{i}Site list@{ui}
- @{b}Delete@{ub} a selected @{i}Site@{ui} from your @{i}Site list@{ui}
- @{b}Save@{ub} the @{i}Site list@{ui} @{u}(only on @{b}registered@{ub} version)@{uu}

- @{b}Add@{ub} the request to the @{i}requests list@{ui}
- @{b}Delete@{ub} a selected request from the @{i}requests list@{ui}
- @{b}Update@{ub} a selected request in the @{i}requests list@{ui}
- @{b}Save@{ub} the filerequests @{u}(only on @{b}registered@{ub} version)@{uu}

- To exit the program click on the @{b}Quit@{ub} gadget

@endnode

